20 SECTION 3. Section 11.11 of S.L. 2022-74, as amended by Section 11.11 of S.L.
21 2023-134, reads as rewritten:
22 "SECTION 11.11.(a) Purpose. – It is in the best economic and developmental interests of
23 the State to support the development of megasites to ensure the State's ongoing competitiveness
24 for major manufacturing opportunities, including, but not limited to, the aerospace, automotive,
25 clean energy, food processing, semiconductor, and life science industries. The purpose of this
26 section is to establish a competitive grant program serving to do the following:
27 (1) Identify and evaluate up to seven megasites for preferred development and
28 marketing.
29 (2) Assist local governments or a partnership of local governments in the
30 acquisition of a newly identified or existing megasite.
31 (3) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to analyze,
32 plan, install, or upgrade public infrastructure, including publicly owned water,
33 gas, and sewer systems, transportation infrastructure, and the electrical utility
34 lines electric infrastructure necessary to meet the needs of prospective
35 employers for megasites.
36 (4) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to fund
37 on-site preparation, including clearing, grading, or other related expenses for
38 megasites.
39 (4a) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments in
40 conducting due diligence, including, but not limited to, the following: site
41 characteristics, preliminary engineering reports for water and wastewater
42 provision to the site, assessments related to road and highway infrastructure
43 to serve the site, and other assessments as needed.
44 (5) Facilitate coordination between the economic development entities, the North
45 Carolina Department of Environmental Quality, and the North Carolina
46 Department of Transportation to expedite needs related to timely site
47 development.
48 …
49 "SECTION 11.11.(c) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
50 …
