18 the local government in exchange for a grant from the Fund. Monies may only
19 be granted for, and used to acquire, a megasite for which (i) one or more local
20 governments have a binding option or offer to purchase and (ii) all basic due
21 diligence must be complete, including, but not limited to, boundary surveys,
22 title searches, State Historic Preservation Office reviews, and wetlands
23 delineation.
24 …
25 "SECTION 11.11.(f) Agreements Required. – Monies may shall be disbursed from the Fund
26 to EDPNC on a quarterly basis in four equal installments per year. EDPNC may use funds only
27 in accordance with agreements entered into between EDPNC and a local government or a
28 government partnership. The agreement must include all of the performance criteria, remedies,
29 and other safeguards required to secure the assistance provided to ready the megasite for a major
30 employer and must require EDPNC to recapture a proportionate amount of assistance provided
31 under this section for failure by a local government or government partnership to meet and
32 maintain the megasite for availability for the purposes for which the assistance was provided.
33 …."
