23 "SECTION 11.12.(e) Allocation. – EDPNC shall allocate monies in the Fund on the
24 following basis:
25 (1) Unspent funds transferred pursuant to subsection (a) of this section shall be
26 used for engaging a national site selection firm through a competitive bid
27 process to produce a report identifying and evaluating 15 selectsites for
28 preferred development and marketing, of which seven must be less than 500
29 acres and of which an additional two must be less than 100 acres. Further
30 unspent funds transferred pursuant to subsection (a) of this section shall be
31 used for engaging a national site selection firm through a competitive bid
32 process to produce a supplemental report identifying and evaluating up to five,
33 and no less than three, additional selectsites from the initial disaster declared
34 counties resulting from Tropical Storm Helene.
35 (2) Funds appropriated to the Fund for local government grants shall be allocated
36 for the purposes outlined in subdivisions (b)(2), (b)(3), (b)(4), and (b)(5) of
37 this section for selectsites determined pursuant to subdivision (1) of this
38 subsection. EDPNC shall prioritize local government grants that have the
39 greatest potential to reduce the time for site readiness and reduce the risk of
40 unforeseen conditions that could affect the site viability for advanced
41 manufacturing projects. EDPNC shall base the grant amount on total
42 development needs for the selectsite, prior investment in the selectsite by one
43 or more local governments, the ability of one or more local governments to
44 invest in the selectsite, and the ability and level of participation promised by
45 the local government in exchange for a grant from the Fund. Monies may only
46 be granted for, and used to acquire, a selectsite for which (i) one or more local
47 governments have a binding option or offer to purchase and (ii) all basic due
48 diligence has been completed, including, but not limited to, boundary surveys,
49 title searches, State Historic Preservation Office reviews, and wetlands
50 delineation.
